 Not sure if this counts as a trick, and I am sure it is not very original...but anyway here goes!<br>
<br>
 I've found that setting up a social key for pick pocket and evade is alot easier than doing it the old way.  <br>
 For example:<br>
 (Line one) /attack off<br>
 (line two) /doability 1 (assuming Hide is number 1 on your ablities list)<br>
 (line three) /attack on<br>
 <br>
 (All in one key <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <br>
<br>
 This at least always gaurantees that you will not accidentally hide or pick pocket while attack is on, which can happen if you try to quickly turn off attack and hide.  <br>
 Well I hope it helps you as much as it did me!<br>
 -Pasai- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uspidor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spidor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/waterchaos.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/7/01 12:09:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidor.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evade and Pickpocket</span><hr size=1> You can also put them both in one macro. You have five lines on each macro, and you have to be out of combat mode for both... SO...<br>
(The name of the skill is used in place of whatever skill number slot you may have it. Use the number of the slot the skill is in, not the name of the skill. Pasai said that already, but it's important enough to repeat, IMHO.)<br>
<br>
/attack off<br>
/doability (pickpocket)<br>
/doability (hide, in order to evade)<br>
/doability (sense traps)<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
That makes sure a skill that normally doesn't get much use (sense traps) also gets a workout.<br>
Sometimes, after using the hide skill, or other combat prohibitive skills, there's a minor delay before you can turn autoattack back on. To get around this, include a /pause in the line just before the /attack on line... a pause of 2 is sufficient to allow the attack command to work.<br>
<br>
Note that you can use this to improve other skills too, such as sense heading, intimidate, disarm, etc. Mix and match, make several different macros. Make one for duelling that includes disarm and instill doubt. Play a little bit, and see what you can come up with!<br>
<br>
I like to make a macro just for building sense heading; note that you have to use the /pause command for it, and a pause of 20 works to reset the skill and let it work again...<br>
<br>
/pause 20,/doability (sense heading)<br>
/pause 20,/doability (sense heading)<br>
/pause 20,/doability (sense heading)<br>
/pause 20,/doability (sense heading)<br>
/pause 20,/doability (sense heading)<br>
<br>
Note the comma has to be there, and so does the slash, but there's no space between them. Pause is the only command that stacks like this; sorry. Note also that it doesn't matter if the /pause command is before the /doability... the actual pause takes place after the /doability command. In this way, you only have to use a macro once in the same space of time you'd normally have to use the skill 5 times. Very handy. <p>Spidor (Redeemed)

