<br>
/attack off<br>
/do # (where # is the ability number you have hide mapped to)<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
As spidor suggests, there is little reason not to combine this action with others to work other skills while evading (pick pocket and sense traps are good suggestions).<br>
<br>
A couple of questions regarding macros:<br>
<br>
Is there a way to make a macro that would allow one to attempt to hide repeatedly? This issue is that you must move in order to get hide button to pop up so a sequence of /do # (hide) does not work (not even including pauses). Anyone know of a command line in a macro that could cause the toon to break hide like this? Ideally, one could use a command that would cause you to jump, a la:<br>
<br>
/do # (hide)<br>
/jump<br>
/pause 7<br>
/do # (hide)<br>
etc<br>
<br>
except there is no /jump command. :-(<br>
<br>
I have an evade/pp macro set up (going to add sense traps to it - thx spidor ;-); but I never get hide skillups when I use it. Any idea why this is so? Macro currently looks like:<br>
<br>
/attack off<br>
/do # (pickpocket)<br>
/do # (hide)<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
Evade works doing it this way, but hide never gets a skillup. Just wondering if anyone knows why or how I could change this macro so as to get a skill up check on hide while evading.<br>
